Source:
  - Title: Treasury of Traditional Wisdom
    Page: 318
  - Title: Laws
    Location: 899 A
By: Plato
Tags:
  - Combat-Action=Symbolism=Solar Symbolism
Commentary:
  Text: The traditional distinction of intelligible from sensible,
    invisible from visible “suns” is essential to any adequate
    understanding of “solar mythologies” and “solar cults”.
  Source:
    Title: Am I My Brother's Keeper
    By: Coomaraswamy
    Page: 92
---
And this Soul of the sun, which is therefore better than the sun,
whether taking the sun about in a chariot to give light to men, or
acting from without, or in whatever way, ought by every man to be
deemed a God.
